(window["webpackJsonp"]=window["webpackJsonp"]||[]).push([["chunk-2d21f0ca"],{d7bc:function(a){a.exports=JSON.parse('{"title":"Prakrta-rasa-sata-dusani","code":"en-Prakrta-rasa-sata-dusani","chapters":[{"title":"","paragraphs":[{"class":"b34","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b35","text":" All glory to Śrī Guru and Śrī Gaurāṅga"},{"class":"b36","text":" Prakrta-rasa-sata-dusani"},{"class":"b42","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">One Hundred Refutations of Mundane Rasa</span>"},{"class":"b37","text":" <span class=\\"e7\\">by</span>"},{"class":"b38","text":" Srila Bhakti Siddhanta Saraswati Thakur"}]},{"title":"Contents","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b47","text":" Contents"},{"class":"b48","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">Introduction</span>"},{"class":"b48","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">Translator’s Note</span>"},{"class":"b48","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">Overview</span>"},{"class":"b48","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">Glossary</span>"},{"class":"b49","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">Prakrta-rasa-sata-dusani</span>"}]},{"title":"Introduction","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b47","text":" Introduction"},{"class":"b43","text":" Amongst the higher classes of humans in the world, there are three paths for travelling through the realm of belief in the afterlife. These are known as karma, jnan, and bhakti. The means for souls in the conditioned state to attain temporary enjoyable ends is known as the path of karma. Rejecting transience and temporary provincial ends and enquiring into nondifferentiated spirit is known as the path of jnan. Transcendental to karma, jnan, and matter, endeavouring to please the rightful recipient of all service Sri Krishna is known as the path of bhakti."},{"class":"b44","text":" Between the means and the end on the path of bhakti, three stages are seen: sadhana, bhava, and prema-bhakti. If we think that the bhavas and prema of the end are practices that are part of the means, trouble arises. Deliverance from the hands of this hindrance is known as anartha-nivrtti. The unprecedented and extraordinary Pastimes of Sri Gaurasundar and the practices and teachings of the goswamis who were His assistants in His Pastimes are the basis of this composition."},{"class":"b52","text":" Sri Siddhanta Saraswati"}]},{"title":"Translator’s Note","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b47","text":" Translator’s Note"},{"class":"b55","text":" The purpose of Srila Bhakti Siddhanta Saraswati Thakur’s <span class=\\"e3\\">Prakrta-rasa-sata-dusani</span> is to clarify the proper understanding and application of the science of rasa given by Srila Rupa Goswami Prabhu in his <span class=\\"e3\\">Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu</span>. Srila Saraswati Thakur wrote this treatise for an audience that is familiar with the key terms given in <span class=\\"e3\\">Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu</span>, and thus he has not defined these terms within his composition. For readers who are not acquainted with these terms and their definitions as given by Srila Rupa Goswami, both an overview of them based on <span class=\\"e3\\">Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu</span> and a glossary are being presented here prior to <span class=\\"e3\\">Prakrta-rasa-sata-dusani</span>. Furthermore, these key terms have for the most part been left untranslated throughout this rendering of <span class=\\"e3\\">Prakrta-rasa-sata-dusani</span> so that readers can clearly see how Srila Bhakti Siddhanta Saraswati Thakur delineates their significance and proper application."}]},{"title":"Overview","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b47","text":" Overview"},{"class":"b50","text":" What is bhakti?"},{"class":"b59","text":" sarvopadhi-vinirmuktam tat-paratvena nirmalam<br />hrsikena hrsikesa-sevanam bhaktir uchyate"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Narada-pancharatra; Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu: Purva-vibhaga, 1.12)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Bhakti is said to be service with the senses to the Lord of the senses that is dedicated to the Lord, unalloyed, and completely unconditional.”"},{"class":"b59","text":" anyabhilasita-sunyam jnana-karmady-anavrtam<br />anukulyena krsnanusilanam bhaktir uttama"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu: Purva-vibhaga, 1.11)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “Pure bhakti is constant endeavour to please Krishna that is free from fleeting desires and unobstructed by exploitation and renunciation.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" What are the distinguishing characteristics of bhakti?"},{"class":"b59","text":" klesa-ghni subhada moksa-laghuta-krt sudurlabha<br />sandrananda-visesatma sri-krsnakarsini cha sa"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu: Purva-vibhaga, 1.17)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “Bhakti (1) destroys all suffering, (2) bestows all good fortune, (3) belittles liberation, (4) is very difficult to attain, (5) is intensely joyful, and (6) attracts Sri Krishna Himself.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" What are the stages of bhakti?"},{"class":"b59","text":" sa bhaktih sadhanam bhavah prema cheti tridhodita"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu: Purva-vibhaga, 2.1)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “Bhakti is said to have three stages: sadhana-bhakti, bhava-bhakti, and prema-bhakti."},{"class":"b50","text":" What is sadhana-bhakti?"},{"class":"b59","text":" krti-sadhya bhavet sadhya-bhava sa sadhanabhidha<br />nitya-siddhasya bhavasya prakatyam hrdi sadhyata"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu: Purva-vibhaga, 2.2)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “Action of the senses aimed at attaining bhava is known as sadhana-bhakti. Such attainment is the manifestation within the heart of one’s perfected eternal nature.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" How many kinds of sadhana-bhakti are there?"},{"class":"b59","text":" vaidhi raganuga cheti sa dvidha sadhanabhidha"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu: Purva-vibhaga, 2.5)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “There are two kinds of sadhana-bhakti: vaidhi and raganuga.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" What is vaidhi-bhakti?"},{"class":"b59","text":" yatra raganavaptatvat pravrttir upajayate<br />sasanenaiva sastrasya sa vaidhi bhaktir uchyate"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu: Purva-vibhaga, 2.6)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “Sadhana-bhakti in which activity arises not from having developed raga but from the regulations of the scriptures is called vaidhi-bhakti.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" What is raga?"},{"class":"b59","text":" iste svarasiki ragah paramavistata bhavet<br />tan-mayi ya bhaved bhaktih satra ragatmikodita"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu: Purva-vibhaga, 2.270)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “Intense natural immersion in the object of one’s desire is called <span class=\\"e3\\">raga</span>. Devotion based on such raga is called <span class=\\"e3\\">ragatmika-bhakti</span>.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" What is raganuga-bhakti?"},{"class":"b59","text":" virajantim abhivyaktam vraja-vasi-janadisu<br />ragatmikam anusrta ya sa raganugochyate"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu: Purva-vibhaga, 2.268)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “Devotion that follows the ragatmika-bhakti beautifully manifest in the residents of Vraja is known as <span class=\\"e3\\">raganuga-bhakti</span>.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" What is bhava-bhakti?"},{"class":"b59","text":" suddha-sattva-visesatma prema-suryamsu-samya-bhak<br />ruchibhis chitta-masrnya-krd asau bhava uchyate"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu: Purva-vibhaga, 3.1)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “Devotion that is completely pure in nature (a special composition of the Lord’s spiritual energy), resembles a ray of the sun of prema, and melts the heart with ruchi is called bhava-bhakti.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" What are the characteristics of bhava-bhakti?"},{"class":"b59","text":" ksantir avyartha-kalatvam viraktir mana-sunyata<br />asa-bandhah samutkantha nama-gane sada ruchih<br />asaktis tad-gunakhyane pritis tad-vasati-sthale<br />ity adayo ’nubhavah syur jata-bhavankure jane"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu: Purva-vibhaga, 3.25–6)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “(1) Tolerance, (2) not wasting time, (3) detachment, (4) pridelessness, (5) hopefulness, (6) longing, (7) constant taste for chanting the Name, (8) attachment to discussion of the Lord’s qualities, and (9) fondness for the Lord’s abode—these and other qualities are present within those in whose hearts bhava has sprouted.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" What is rati?"},{"class":"b59","text":" purane natya-sastre cha dvayos tu rati-bhavayoh<br />samanarthataya hy atra dvayam aikyena laksitam"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu: Purva-vibhaga, 3.13)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “In the Puranas and the scriptures on drama, the words <span class=\\"e3\\">rati</span> and <span class=\\"e3\\">bhava</span> have the same meaning. Here also (in <span class=\\"e3\\">Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu</span>), the two words are seen to be synonymous.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" What is prema?"},{"class":"b59","text":" samyan-masrnita-svanto mamatvatisayankitah<br />bhavah sa eva sandratma budhaih prema nigadyate"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu: Purva-vibhaga, 4.1)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “Intense bhava that completely melts the heart and is characterised by extreme loving possessiveness (of the Lord) is called prema by the wise.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" What are the stages in the awakenment of prema?"},{"class":"b59","text":" adau sraddha tatah sadhu-sango ’tha bhajana-kriya<br />tato’nartha-nivrttih syat tato nistha ruchis tatah<br />athasaktis tato bhavas tatah premabhyudanchati<br />sadhakanam ayam premnah pradurbhave bhavet kramah"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu: Purva-vibhaga, 4.15–6)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “First sraddha, then sadhu-sanga, then bhajana-kriya, then anartha-nivrtti, then nistha, then ruchi, then asakti, then bhava, and then prema arise. These are the stages in a practitioner’s prema arising.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" What is sraddha?"},{"class":"b71","text":" Faith in revealed truth produced by association with sadhus and both knowing and unknowing engagement in service to the Lord; faith that by serving Krishna all duties and desires are fulfilled."},{"class":"b50","text":" What is sadhu-sanga?"},{"class":"b71","text":" Taking shelter at the feet of Sri Guru and learning the process of service to the Lord under his guidance; associating with and serving the sadhus, those who adhere to truth."},{"class":"b50","text":" What is bhajana-kriya?"},{"class":"b71","text":" Engaging in practices of devotion, such as hearing, chanting, and worshipping, according to the instructions of Sri Guru and the sadhus."},{"class":"b50","text":" What is anartha-nivrtti?"},{"class":"b71","text":" The gradual cessation of the four types of vices—(1) misconception, (2) desires for the mundane, (3) offences, and (4) weakness of heart."},{"class":"b50","text":" What is nistha?"},{"class":"b71","text":" Constant engagement in the service of the Lord free from anarthas and distractions."},{"class":"b50","text":" What is ruchi?"},{"class":"b71","text":" Genuine taste for the Lord and His service."},{"class":"b50","text":" What is asakti?"},{"class":"b71","text":" Attachment; natural ruchi for the Lord and His service."},{"class":"b50","text":" What are bhava and prema?"},{"class":"b71","text":" These have been defined above in <span class=\\"e3\\">Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu</span>: Purva-vibhaga, 3.1 and 4.1."},{"class":"b50","text":" What is rasa?"},{"class":"b59","text":" vyatitya bhavana-vartma yas chamatkara-bhara-bhuh<br />hrdi sattvojjvale badham svadate sa raso matah"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu: Daksina-vibhaga, 5.132)"},{"class":"b43","text":" “That which is beyond the scope of thought, extremely wonderful, and most deeply relished in a heart shining with pure goodness is known as rasa.”"},{"class":"b44","text":" In further detail:"},{"class":"b69","text":" “That which surpasses all thought of its ingredients, is more wonderful than rati (bhava-bhakti), and is most deeply relished in a heart made bright by a special manifestation of the Lord’s spiritual energy is known as rasa.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" Who is Krishna?"},{"class":"b59","text":" akhila-rasamrta-murtih"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu: Purva-vibhaga, 1.1)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “Krishna is the the personification of the supreme joy, the abode of all spiritual rasas.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" What is the Name?"},{"class":"b59","text":" nama-chintamanih krsnas chaitanya-rasa-vigrahah<br />purnah suddho nitya-mukto ‘bhinnatvan nama-naminoh"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu: Purva-vibhaga, 2.233)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “The Name of Krishna is a wish-fulfilling jewel and an embodiment of spiritual rasa. The Name is complete, pure, eternally liberated, and non-different from whom He names.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" How is the Name revealed?"},{"class":"b59","text":" atah sri-krsna-namadi na bhaved grahyam indriyaih<br />sevonmukhe hi jihvadau svayam eva sphuraty adah"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu: Purva-vibhaga, 2.234)"},{"class":"b55","text":" “Although Krishna’s Name, Form, Qualities, and Pastimes cannot be grasped by the material senses, they manifest themselves to the material senses in response to one’s inclination to serve.”"}]},{"title":"Glossary","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b47","text":" Glossary"},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">abhidheya:</span> the means to the end; the practice of devotion, and mainly, the stage of sadhana-bhakti."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">anarthas:</span> misconceptions, desires for the mundane, offences, and weaknesses of heart."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha-nivrtti:</span> the gradual cessation of anarthas and development of nistha."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">aprakrta:</span> lit. ‘not mundane’; supramundane, divine, spiritual; something part of, or related to, the highest plane of spiritual existence, the land of Lord Krishna’s Pastimes, which at times resembles the mundane world but is nevertheless ‘not mundane’."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">aparadha:</span> offence; an action that is contrary to the rules, principles, or mood of devotion to the Lord; an action that displeases the Lord; substandard worship."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">asakti:</span> attachment; natural ruchi for the Lord and His service."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajana-kriya:</span> engaging in practices of devotion, such as hearing, chanting, and serving, according to the instructions of Sri Guru and the sadhus."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti:</span> service to the Supreme Lord rendered solely unconditionally, and constantly for His pleasure."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava (bhava-bhakti):</span> devotion composed of the Lord’s spiritual energy (the samvit- and hladini-saktis) that resembles a ray of the sun of prema-bhakti and melts the heart with ruchi; the second of the three stages of bhakti, following sadhana-bhakti and preceding prema-bhakti."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">guru:</span> lit. ‘heavy’; master, teacher; one who dispels darkness; the form the Supreme Lord assumes to distribute divine knowledge."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">krama-patha:</span> the gradual path; the path given by Srila Rupa Goswami in <span class=\\"e3\\">Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu</span> (Purva-vibhaga, 4.15–6) for the development of prema-bhakti which contains nine general stages: sraddha, sadhu-sanga, bhajana-kriya, anartha-nivrtti, nistha, ruchi, asakti, bhava, and finally prema. <span class=\\"e3\\">Krama-patha</span> also in some cases refers to the gradual process by which the Lord reveals Himself sequentially as His nama, rupa, guna, and then lila—His Name, then His form, then His qualities, and finally His Pastimes."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nama:</span> lit. ‘name’; the Name of the Supreme Lord; the personal form of the Lord as His Name, nondifferent from the Lord Himself."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nistha:</span> constant engagement in the service of the Lord free from anarthas."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prakrti:</span> material energy."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prakrta:</span> material, made of or based on material energy."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prayojan:</span> the goal; the highest attainment: Sri Krishna-prema."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prema (prema-bhakti):</span> divine love; extremely intense bhava that completely melts the heart and produces intense feelings of loving possessiveness for the Lord."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">raga:</span> intense natural immersion in the object of one’s desire, one’s worshippable master."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">raganuga:</span> a practitioner of raganuga-bhakti."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">raganuga (raganuga-bhakti):</span> devotion that follows the devotion of the residents of Vraja, whose devotion is based purely on raga."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa:</span> the inconceivable, wonderful taste within service to the Lord found in the hearts of pure devotees; rati (sthayi-bhava) brought into the heart by hearing, chanting, and other practices of devotion and nourished by vibhavas, anubhavas, sattvika-bhavas, and vyabhichari-bhavas."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">rasika:</span> a devotee in the stage of bhava-bhakti or prema-bhakti who has genuine experience of rasa."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">rati:</span> a synonym for bhava and sthayi-bhava."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ruchi:</span> genuine taste for the Lord and His service that arises on the basis of nistha."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">Rupa (Sri):</span> Srila Rupa Goswami, the author <span class=\\"e3\\">Sri Bhakti-rasamrta-sindhu</span> and the foremost authority on the science of rasa."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sadhaka:</span> practitioner, esp. one engaged in the practice of sadhana-bhakti."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sadhana (sadhana-bhakti):</span> engagement of the senses in devotional practices aimed at uncovering the eternal nature of the soul; the first of the three stages of bhakti, followed by bhava-bhakti and prema-bhakti. (Brs: 1.2.2)"},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sadhu:</span> one who is adherent to truth, that is, devoted to the Lord and His service."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sadhu-sanga:</span> association with and service to sadhus; taking shelter at the feet of Sri Guru and being initiated and trained by Sri Guru in service to the Lord and all that is dear to Him."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sahajiyaism:</span> imitationism; imitating the behaviour of those who have rati and taste rasa and/or wrongly believe that one has rati and tastes rasa when in fact one does not."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sambandha-jnan:</span> knowledge of the Supreme Lord, His energies, and their relationships; the foundation of the practice of devotion."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">siddhanta:</span> proper conclusions and conceptions; the essence of the teachings of the sadhus and scriptures."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sisya:</span> a disciple, one who accepts discipline."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sraddha:</span> faith in revealed truth produced by association with sadhus; faith that by serving Krishna all duties and desires are fulfilled."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sthayi-bhava:</span> foundational rati for Krishna, which has any one of five primary forms: santa, dasya, sakhya, vatsalya, and madhura [adoration, servitude, friendship, affectionate guardianship, and paramour love]."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vaidhi:</span> based on the regulations of the scriptures."},{"class":"b55","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vaidhi-bhakti:</span> sadhana-bhakti based on the regulations of the scriptures (rather than on raga)."}]},{"title":"Prakrta-rasa-sata-dusani","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b47","text":" Prakrta-rasa-sata-dusani"},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রাকৃত-চেষ্টাতে ভাই কভু রস হয় না<br />জড়ীয় প্রাকৃতরস শুদ্ধভক্ত গায় না ॥১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prakrta-chestate bhai kabhu rasa haya na<br />jadiya prakrta-rasa suddha-bhakta gaya na [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhai</span>–O brother! <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–Rasa <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–arises [from] <span class=\\"e2\\">prakrta</span>–material <span class=\\"e2\\">chestate</span>–endeavours. <span class=\\"e2\\">suddha</span>–Pure <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span>–devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">gaya na</span>–do not sing [about] <span class=\\"e2\\">jadiya</span>–mundane <span class=\\"e2\\">prakrta</span>–material <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasa. [1]"},{"class":"b50","text":" O brother! Rasa never arises from material endeavours. Pure devotees do not sing about mundane material rasa."},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রাকৃতরসের শিক্ষা-ভিক্ষা শিষ্যে চায় না<br />রতি বিনা যেই রস তাহা গুরু দেয় না ॥২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prakrta-rasera siksa-bhiksa sisye chaya na<br />rati vina yei rasa taha guru deya na [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sisye</span>–A disciple <span class=\\"e2\\">chaya na</span>–does not desire <span class=\\"e2\\">bhiksa</span>–alms [in the form] <span class=\\"e2\\">siksa</span>–of teachings [about] <span class=\\"e2\\">prakrta</span>–mundane <span class=\\"e2\\">rasera</span>–rasa. <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–A Guru <span class=\\"e2\\">deya na</span>–does not give <span class=\\"e2\\">taha</span>–such <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasa <span class=\\"e2\\">yei</span>–that [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">vina</span>–devoid of <span class=\\"e2\\">rati</span>–rati. [2]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A disciple does not desire alms in the form of teachings about mundane rasa. A Guru does not give rasa that is devoid of rati."},{"class":"b97","text":" নাম রস দুই বস্তু ভক্ত কভু জানে না<br />নাম রসে ভেদ আছে ভক্ত কভু বলে না ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nama rasa dui vastu bhakta kabhu jane na<br />nama rase bheda achhe bhakta kabhu bale na [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span>–A devotee <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">jane</span>–considers <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–the Name [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasa <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span>–two [different] <span class=\\"e2\\">vastu</span>–things. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span>–A devotee <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says <span class=\\"e2\\">achhe</span>–there is <span class=\\"e2\\">bheda</span>–a difference [between] <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–the Name [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">rase</span>–rasa. [3]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A devotee never considers the Name and rasa two different things. A devotee never says there is a difference between the Name and rasa."},{"class":"b97","text":" অহং-মম-ভাবসত্ত্বে নাম কভু হয় না<br />ভোগ-বুদ্ধি না ছাড়িলে অপ্রাকৃত হয় না ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" aham-mama-bhava-sattve nama kabhu haya na<br />bhoga-buddhi na chhadile aprakrta haya na [4]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–The Name <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–manifests [to those] <span class=\\"e2\\">sattve</span>–in the condition <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava</span>–of thought <span class=\\"e2\\">aham</span>–of ‘I’ [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">mama</span>–‘mine’. <span class=\\"e2\\">chhadile na</span>–If one does not give up <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhi</span>–the mentality <span class=\\"e2\\">bhoga</span>–of enjoying, <span class=\\"e2\\">aprakrta</span>–transcendence (‘supramundanity’) <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–does not manifest. [4]"},{"class":"b50","text":" The Name never manifests to those who have the mentality of ‘I’ and ‘mine’. If one does not give up the enjoying mentality, transcendence does not manifest."},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রাকৃত জড়ের ভোগে কৃষ্ণসেবা হয় না<br />জড়বস্তু কোনও কালে অপ্রাকৃত হয় না ॥৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prakrta jadera bhoge krsna-seva haya na<br />jada-vastu konao kale aprakrta haya na [5]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">seva</span>–Service <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–to Krishna <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–does not occur <span class=\\"e2\\">bhoge</span>–by enjoyment [of] <span class=\\"e2\\">prakrta</span>–mundane <span class=\\"e2\\">jadera</span>–matter, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–material <span class=\\"e2\\">vastu</span>–objects <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–do not become <span class=\\"e2\\">aprakrta</span>–supramundane [at] <span class=\\"e2\\">konao</span>–any <span class=\\"e2\\">kale</span>–time. [5]"},{"class":"b50","text":" Krishna is not served by mundane material enjoyment, and material objects never become supramundane."},{"class":"b97","text":" জড়সত্ত্বা বর্ত্তমানে চিৎ কভু হয় না<br />জড়বস্তু চিৎ হয় ভক্তে কভু বলে না ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jada-sattva vartamane chit kabhu haya na<br />jada-vastu chit haya bhakte kabhu bale na [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">chit</span>–Spirit <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–manifests <span class=\\"e2\\">vartamane</span>–in the presence <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–of the material <span class=\\"e2\\">sattva</span>–existence, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakte</span>–a devotee <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–material <span class=\\"e2\\">vastu</span>–objects <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–become <span class=\\"e2\\">chit</span>–spirit. [6]"},{"class":"b50","text":" Spirit never manifests in the presence of matter, and a devotee never says material objects become spiritual."},{"class":"b97","text":" জড়ীয় বিষয়-ভোগ ভক্ত কভু করে না<br />জড়ভোগ কৃষ্ণসেবা কভু সম হয় না ॥৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jadiya visaya-bhoga bhakta kabhu kare na<br />jada-bhoga krsna-seva kabhu sama haya na [7]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span>–A devotee <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–engages in <span class=\\"e2\\">bhoga</span>–enjoyment [of] <span class=\\"e2\\">jadiya</span>–material <span class=\\"e2\\">visaya</span>–objects. <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–Material <span class=\\"e2\\">bhoga</span>–enjoyment [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">seva</span>–service <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–to Krishna <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–are <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">sama</span>–the same. [7]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A devotee never engages in enjoyment of material objects. Material enjoyment and service to Krishna are never the same thing."},{"class":"b97","text":" নিজ-ভোগ্য কামে ভক্ত প্রেম কভু বলে না<br />রসে ডগমগ আছ শিষ্যে গুরু বলে না ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nija-bhogya kame bhakta prema kabhu bale na<br />rase dagamaga achha sisye guru bale na [8]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span>–A devotee <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says <span class=\\"e2\\">kame</span>–desire <span class=\\"e2\\">nija</span>–for one’s own <span class=\\"e2\\">bhogya</span>–enjoyment [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">prema</span>–divine love. <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–A Guru <span class=\\"e2\\">bale na</span>–does not tell <span class=\\"e2\\">sisye</span>–a disciple, <span class=\\"e2\\">achha</span>–“You are <span class=\\"e2\\">dagamaga</span>–absorbed <span class=\\"e2\\">rase</span>–in rasa.” [8]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A devotee never says desire for one’s own enjoyment is prema. A Guru does not tell a disciple, “You are absorbed in rasa.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" রসে ডগমগ আমি কভু গুরু বলে না<br />জড়ীয় রসের কথা শিষ্যে গুরু বলে না ॥৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" rase dagamaga ami kabhu guru bale na<br />jadiya rasera katha sisye guru bale na [9]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–A Guru <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says, <span class=\\"e2\\">ami</span>–“I [am] <span class=\\"e2\\">dagamaga</span>–absorbed <span class=\\"e2\\">rase</span>–in rasa.” <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–A Guru <span class=\\"e2\\">katha bale na</span>–does not discuss <span class=\\"e2\\">jadiya</span>–material <span class=\\"e2\\">rasera</span>–rasa <span class=\\"e2\\">sisye</span>–with a disciple. [9]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A Guru never says, “I am absorbed in rasa.” A Guru does not discuss material rasa with a disciple."},{"class":"b97","text":" জড়রস-গানে কভু শ্রেয়ঃ কেহ লভে না<br />কৃষ্ণকে প্রাকৃত বলি’ ভক্ত কভু গায় না ॥১০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jada-rasa-gane kabhu sreyah keha labhe na<br />krsnake prakrta bali’ bhakta kabhu gaya na [10]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">keha na</span>–No one <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span>–ever <span class=\\"e2\\">labhe</span>–attains <span class=\\"e2\\">sreyah</span>–good fortune <span class=\\"e2\\">gane</span>–by singing [about] <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–material <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasa. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span>–A devotee <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">gaya</span>–sings <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span>–considering <span class=\\"e2\\">krsnake</span>–Krishna <span class=\\"e2\\">prakrta</span>–mundane. [10]"},{"class":"b50","text":" No one ever attains good fortune by singing about material rasa. A devotee never sings of Krishna being mundane."},{"class":"b97","text":" নামকে প্রাকৃত বলি’ কৃষ্ণে জড় জানে না<br />কৃষ্ণনামরসে ভেদ শুদ্ধভক্ত মানে না ॥১১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" namake prakrta bali’ krsne jada jane na<br />krsna-nama-rase bheda suddha-bhakta mane na [11]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">suddha</span>–A pure <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span>–devotee <span class=\\"e2\\">jane na</span>–does not think <span class=\\"e2\\">krsne</span>–Krishna [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–material [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span>–say <span class=\\"e2\\">namake</span>–the Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">prakrta</span>–mundane. <span class=\\"e2\\">mane na</span>–They do not recognise <span class=\\"e2\\">bheda</span>–a distinction <span class=\\"e2\\">rase</span>–between rasa, <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–the Name, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–Krishna. [11]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A pure devotee does not think Krishna is material or say the Name is mundane. They do not recognise a distinction between rasa, the Name, and Krishna."},{"class":"b97","text":" নামরসে ভেদ আছে গুরু শিক্ষা দেয় না<br />রস লাভ করি’ শেষে সাধন ত হয় না ॥১২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nama-rase bheda achhe guru siksa deya na<br />rasa labha kari’ sese sadhana ta haya na [12]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–A Guru <span class=\\"e2\\">siksa deya na</span>–does not teach [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">achhe</span>–there is <span class=\\"e2\\">bheda</span>–a distinction <span class=\\"e2\\">rase</span>–between rasa [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–the Name, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">ta</span>–indeed <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–it is not [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">labha kari’</span>–one will attain <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasa [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sese</span>–afterwards [take up] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadhana</span>–the practice. [12]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A Guru does not teach that there is a distinction between rasa and the Name, and it is not that one will attain rasa and afterwards take up sadhana."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃত্রিম পন্থায় নামে রসোদয় হয় না<br />রস হৈতে কৃষ্ণনাম বিলোমেতে হয় না ॥১৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" krtrima panthaya name rasodaya haya na<br />rasa haite krsna-nama vilomete haya na [13]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–Rasa<span class=\\"e2\\"> udaya haya na</span>–does not arise <span class=\\"e2\\">name</span>–from the Name [on] <span class=\\"e2\\">krtrima</span>–the false <span class=\\"e2\\">panthaya</span>–path. <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–The Name <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–of Krishna <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–does not arise <span class=\\"e2\\">haite</span>–from <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasa <span class=\\"e2\\">vilomete</span>–in reverse order. [13]"},{"class":"b50","text":" Rasa does not arise from the Name on the false path. The Name of Krishna does not in reverse order arise from rasa."},{"class":"b97","text":" রস হৈতে রতি শ্রদ্ধা কখনই হয় না<br />শ্রদ্ধা হৈতে রতি ছাড়া ভাগবত গায় না ॥১৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" rasa haite rati sraddha kakhanai haya na<br />sraddha haite rati chhada bhagavata gaya na [14]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">rati</span>–Rati [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sraddha</span>–faith <span class=\\"e2\\">kakhanai haya na</span>–never ever arise <span class=\\"e2\\">haite</span>–from <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasa. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhagavata</span>–A devotee <span class=\\"e2\\">gaya na</span>–does not sing [of anything] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhada</span>–other than <span class=\\"e2\\">rati</span>–rati [that has arisen] <span class=\\"e2\\">haite</span>–from <span class=\\"e2\\">sraddha</span>–faith. [14]"},{"class":"b50","text":" Rati and sraddha never ever arise from rasa. A devotee does not sing of anything other than rati that has arisen from sraddha."},{"class":"b97","text":" রতিযুক্ত রস ছাড়া শুদ্ধভক্ত বলে না<br />সাধনেতে রতি রস গুরু কভু বলে না ॥১৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" rati-yukta rasa chhada suddha-bhakta bale na<br />sadhanete rati rasa guru kabhu bale na [15]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">suddha</span>–A pure <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span>–devotee <span class=\\"e2\\">bale na</span>–does not speak [of anything] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhada</span>–other than <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasa <span class=\\"e2\\">yukta</span>–based <span class=\\"e2\\">rati</span>–on rati. <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–A Guru <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says [there is] <span class=\\"e2\\">rati</span>–rati [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasa <span class=\\"e2\\">sadhanete</span>–in the [stage of] practice. [15]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A pure devotee does not speak of anything other than rasa based on rati. A Guru never says there is rati and rasa in the stage of sadhana."},{"class":"b97","text":" ভাবকালে যে অবস্থা সাধনাগ্রে বলে না<br />বৈধী শ্রদ্ধা সাধনেতে রাগানুগা হয় না ॥১৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhava-kale ye avastha sadhanagre bale na<br />vaidhi sraddha sadhanete raganuga haya na [16]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bale na</span>–A Guru does not say <span class=\\"e2\\">ye avastha</span>–the conditions <span class=\\"e2\\">kale</span>–at the time <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava</span>–of bhava-bhakti [arise] <span class=\\"e2\\">agre</span>–prior <span class=\\"e2\\">sadhana</span>–to sadhana-bhakti. <span class=\\"e2\\">raganuga</span>–Raganuga-bhakti <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–does not develop <span class=\\"e2\\">sadhanete</span>–from <span class=\\"e2\\">sraddha</span>–faith <span class=\\"e2\\">vaidhi</span>–based on [scriptural] regulations. [16]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A Guru does not say that the state reached in the stage of bhava-bhakti arises prior to the stage of sadhana. Raganuga-bhakti does not develop from faith based on scriptural regulations."},{"class":"b97","text":" ভাবের অঙ্কুর হলে বিধি আর থাকে না<br />রাগানুগা শ্রদ্ধা মাত্রে জাতরতি হয় না ॥১৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhavera ankura hale vidhi ara thake na<br />raganuga sraddha matre jata-rati haya na [17]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [When] <span class=\\"e2\\">ankura</span>–the sprout <span class=\\"e2\\">bhavera</span>–of bhava <span class=\\"e2\\">hale</span>–arises, <span class=\\"e2\\">vidhi</span>–regulations <span class=\\"e2\\">ara thake na</span>–no longer remain. <span class=\\"e2\\">jata</span>–Developed <span class=\\"e2\\">rati</span>–rati <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–does not arise <span class=\\"e2\\">matre</span>–only by <span class=\\"e2\\">sraddha</span>–faith <span class=\\"e2\\">raganuga</span>–in raganuga-bhakti. [17]"},{"class":"b50","text":" When the sprout of bhava arises, regulations withdraw. Developed rati does not arise only by faith in raganuga-bhakti."},{"class":"b97","text":" অজাতরতিকে কভু ভাবলব্ধ বলে না<br />রাগানুগ সাধকেরে জাতভাব বলে না ॥১৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ajata-ratike kabhu bhava-labdha bale na<br />raganuga sadhakere jata-bhava bale na [18]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">raganuga</span>–A raganuga-bhakta <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">ajata</span>–undeveloped <span class=\\"e2\\">ratike</span>–rati [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">labdha</span>–realised <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava</span>–bhava, [and they] <span class=\\"e2\\">bale na</span>–do not say [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadhakere</span>–practitioners [have] <span class=\\"e2\\">jata</span>–developed <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava</span>–bhava. [18]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A raganuga-bhakta never says that undeveloped rati is realised bhava, and they do not say that sadhakas have developed bhava."},{"class":"b97","text":" রাগানুগ সাধকেরে লব্ধরস বলে না<br />রাগানুগা সাধ্যভাব রতি ছাড়া হয় না ॥১৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" raganuga sadhakere labdha-rasa bale na<br />raganuga sadhya-bhava rati chhada haya na [19]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">raganuga</span>–A raganuga-bhakta <span class=\\"e2\\">bale na</span>–does not say [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadhakere</span>–practitioners [have] <span class=\\"e2\\">labdha</span>–attained <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasa. <span class=\\"e2\\">sadhya</span>–The perfected <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava</span>–bhava <span class=\\"e2\\">raganuga</span>–of raganuga-bhakti <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–does not arise <span class=\\"e2\\">chhada</span>–without <span class=\\"e2\\">rati</span>–rati. [19]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A raganuga-bhakta does not say that sadhakas have attained rasa. The perfected bhava of raganuga-bhakti does not arise without rati."},{"class":"b97","text":" ভাবাঙ্কুর-সমাগমে বৈধী-ভক্তি থাকে না<br />রুচিকে রতির সহ কভু এক জানে না ॥২০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhavankura-samagame vaidhi-bhakti thake na<br />ruchike ratira saha kabhu eka jane na [20]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">samagame</span>–With the arrival <span class=\\"e2\\">ankura</span>–of the sprout <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava</span>–of bhava, <span class=\\"e2\\">vaidhi</span>–regulated <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti</span>–devotion <span class=\\"e2\\">thake na</span>–does not remain. [A raganuga-bhakta] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">jane</span>–thinks <span class=\\"e2\\">ruchike</span>–ruchi [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span>–one <span class=\\"e2\\">saha</span>–with <span class=\\"e2\\">ratira</span>–rati. [20]"},{"class":"b50","text":" With the arrival of the sprout of bhava, vaidhi-bhakti withdraws. A raganuga-bhakta never thinks ruchi and rati are one and the same."},{"class":"b97","text":" রাগানুগা বলিলেই প্রাপ্তরস জানে না<br />বিধি-শোধ্যজনে কভু রাগানুগ বলে না ॥২১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" raganuga balilei prapta-rasa jane na<br />vidhi-sodhya-jane kabhu raganuga bale na [21]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [A raganuga-bhakta] <span class=\\"e2\\">jane na</span>–does not think [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">balilei</span>–just by saying <span class=\\"e2\\">raganuga</span>–‘raganuga-bhakti’ [one has] <span class=\\"e2\\">prapta</span>–attained <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasa. [A raganuga-bhakta] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says <span class=\\"e2\\">jane</span>–someone [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">sodhya</span>–needs to be purified <span class=\\"e2\\">vidhi</span>–by regulations [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">raganuga</span>–a raganuga-bhakta. [21]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A raganuga-bhakta does not think that just by saying ‘raganuga-bhakti’, one has attained rasa, and a raganuga-bhakta never says someone who needs to be purified by regulations is a raganuga-bhakta."},{"class":"b97","text":" সাধনের পূর্ব্বে কেহ ভাবাঙ্কুর পায় না<br />জড়ে শ্রদ্ধা না ছাড়িলে রতি কভু হয় না ॥২২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sadhanera purve keha bhavankura paya na<br />jade sraddha na chhadile rati kabhu haya na [22]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">keha na</span>–No one <span class=\\"e2\\">paya</span>–feels <span class=\\"e2\\">ankura</span>–the sprout <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava</span>–of bhava <span class=\\"e2\\">purve</span>–prior to <span class=\\"e2\\">sadhanera</span>–practice. <span class=\\"e2\\">rati</span>–Rati <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–arises <span class=\\"e2\\">chhadile na</span>–if one has not given up <span class=\\"e2\\">sraddha</span>–faith <span class=\\"e2\\">jade</span>–in the mundane. [22]"},{"class":"b50","text":" No one feels the sprout of bhava prior to the stage of sadhana-bhakti. Rati never never arises if one has not given up faith in the mundane."},{"class":"b97","text":" জাতভাব না হইলে রসিক ত হয় না<br />জড়ভাব না ছাড়িলে রসিক ত হয় না ॥২৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jata-bhava na ha-ile rasika ta haya na<br />jada-bhava na chhadile rasika ta haya na [23]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [If] <span class=\\"e2\\">jata</span>–developed <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava</span>–bhava <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ile na</span>–has not arisen, <span class=\\"e2\\">ta</span>–indeed <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–one cannot become <span class=\\"e2\\">rasika</span>–a relisher of rasa, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhadile na</span>–if one does not give up <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–mundane <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava</span>–bhava, <span class=\\"e2\\">ta</span>–indeed <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–one cannot become <span class=\\"e2\\">rasika</span>–a relisher of rasa. [23]"},{"class":"b50","text":" If developed bhava has not arisen, one cannot become a rasika, and if one does not give up mundane bhava, one cannot become a rasika."},{"class":"b97","text":" মূলধন রসলাভ রতি বিনা হয় না<br />গাছে না উঠিতে কাঁদি বৃক্ষমূলে পায় না ॥২৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" mula-dhana rasa-labha rati vina haya na<br />gachhe na uthite kadi vrksa-mule paya na [24]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">labha</span>–Attainment <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–of rasa, <span class=\\"e2\\">mula</span>–the foremost <span class=\\"e2\\">dhana</span>–wealth, <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–does not occur <span class=\\"e2\\">vina</span>–without <span class=\\"e2\\">rati</span>–rati. <span class=\\"e2\\">paya na</span>–One cannot attain [it] <span class=\\"e2\\">uthite na</span>–by not climbing <span class=\\"e2\\">gachhe</span>–the tree [and simply] <span class=\\"e2\\">ka̐di</span>–crying <span class=\\"e2\\">mule</span>–at the bottom <span class=\\"e2\\">vrksa</span>–of the tree. [24]"},{"class":"b50","text":" Without rati, there is no attainment of rasa, the foremost wealth. One cannot attain it by not climbing the tree and simply crying at the bottom."},{"class":"b97","text":" সাধনে অনর্থ আছে রসোদয় হয় না<br />ভাবকালে নামগানে ছলরস হয় না ॥২৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sadhane anartha achhe rasodaya haya na<br />bhava-kale nama-gane chhala-rasa haya na [25]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–Rasa<span class=\\"e2\\"> udaya haya na</span>–does not arise [when] <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–vices <span class=\\"e2\\">achhe</span>–are present <span class=\\"e2\\">sadhane</span>–in [one’s] practice. <span class=\\"e2\\">chhala</span>–False <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasa <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–does not arise <span class=\\"e2\\">gane</span>–in chanting <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">kale</span>–at the time <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava</span>–of bhava. [25]"},{"class":"b50","text":" Rasa does not arise when anarthas are present in one’s sadhana. False rasa does not arise in the chanting of the Name in the stage of bhava."},{"class":"b97","text":" সিদ্ধান্তবিহীন হৈলে কৃষ্ণে চিত্ত লাগে না<br />সম্বন্ধহীনের কভু অভিধেয় হয় না ॥২৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" siddhanta-vihina haile krsne chitta lage na<br />sambandha-hinera kabhu abhidheya haya na [26]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">haile</span>–If one is <span class=\\"e2\\">vihina</span>–bereft <span class=\\"e2\\">siddhanta</span>–of a proper conception, <span class=\\"e2\\">chitta</span>–the mind <span class=\\"e2\\">lage na</span>–does not become attached <span class=\\"e2\\">krsne</span>–to Krishna. <span class=\\"e2\\">abhidheya</span>–The process <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–reaches success <span class=\\"e2\\">hinera</span>–for those who are devoid <span class=\\"e2\\">sambandha</span>–of [understanding of the soul’s] relationship [with the Lord]. [26]"},{"class":"b50","text":" If one does not know siddhanta, the mind does not become attached to Krishna. Those who lack sambandha-jnan never succeed in abhidheya."},{"class":"b97","text":" সম্বন্ধবিহীন জন প্রয়োজন পায় না<br />কুসিদ্ধান্তে ব্যস্ত জন কৃষ্ণসেবা করে না ॥২৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sambandha-vihina jana prayojana paya na<br />kusiddhante vyasta jana krsna-seva kare na [27]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–Persons <span class=\\"e2\\">vihina</span>–bereft <span class=\\"e2\\">sambandha</span>–of [understanding of the soul’s] relationship [with the Lord] <span class=\\"e2\\">paya na</span>–do not reach <span class=\\"e2\\">prayojana</span>–the goal. <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–Persons <span class=\\"e2\\">vyasta</span>–preoccupied <span class=\\"e2\\">kusiddhante</span>–with misconception <span class=\\"e2\\">kare na</span>–do not engage in <span class=\\"e2\\">seva</span>–the service <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–of Krishna. [27]"},{"class":"b50","text":" Those who lack sambandha-jnan do not attain prayojan. Those who are preoccupied with misconception do not serve Krishna."},{"class":"b97","text":" সিদ্ধান্ত-অলস জন অনর্থ ত ছাড়ে না<br />জড়ে কৃষ্ণ ভ্রম করি’ কৃষ্ণসেবা করে না ॥২৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" siddhanta-alasa jana anartha ta chhade na<br />jade krsna bhrama kari’ krsna-seva kare na [28]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–Persons [who are] <span class=\\"e2\\">alasa</span>–lazy <span class=\\"e2\\">siddhanta</span>–about [learning] the proper conception <span class=\\"e2\\">ta</span>–indeed <span class=\\"e2\\">chhade na</span>–do not give up [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–vices. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhrama kari’</span>–They confuse <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–Krishna <span class=\\"e2\\">jade</span>–with matter [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kare na</span>–do not engage in <span class=\\"e2\\">seva</span>–the service <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–of Krishna. [28]"},{"class":"b50","text":" Those who are lazy about learning siddhanta do not give up their anarthas. They confuse Krishna with matter and do not engage in Krishna’s service."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণনামে ভক্ত জড়বুদ্ধি কভু করে না<br />অনর্থ না গেলে নামে রূপ দেখা দেয় না ॥২৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" krsna-name bhakta jada-buddhi kabhu kare na<br />anartha na gele name rupa dekha deya na [29]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span>–A devotee <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhi kare</span>–thinks <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–Krishna’s <span class=\\"e2\\">name</span>–Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–material. [If one’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–vices <span class=\\"e2\\">gele na</span>–have not gone away, [Krishna’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">rupa</span>–form <span class=\\"e2\\">dekha deya na</span>–does not reveal [Himself] <span class=\\"e2\\">name</span>–through the Name. [29]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A devotee never thinks Krishna’s Name is material. If one’s anarthas have not gone away, Krishna’s form does not reveal Himself through the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" অনর্থ না গেলে নামে গুণ বুঝা যায় না<br />অনর্থ না গেলে নামে কৃষ্ণসেবা হয় না ॥৩০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" anartha na gele name guna bujha yaya na<br />anartha na gele name krsna-seva haya na [30]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [If one’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–vices <span class=\\"e2\\">gele na</span>–have not gone away, [Krishna’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">guna</span>–qualities <span class=\\"e2\\">bujha yaya na</span>–cannot be understood <span class=\\"e2\\">name</span>–through the Name. [If one’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–vices <span class=\\"e2\\">gele na</span>–have not gone away, <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–there is no <span class=\\"e2\\">seva</span>–service <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–to Krishna <span class=\\"e2\\">name</span>–through the Name. [30]"},{"class":"b50","text":" If one’s anarthas have not gone away, Krishna’s qualities cannot be understood through the Name. If one’s anarthas have not gone away, there is no service to Krishna through the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" রূপ-গুণ-লীলা-স্ফূর্ত্তি নাম ছাড়া হয় না<br />রূপ-গুণ-লীলা হৈতে কৃষ্ণনাম হয় না ॥৩১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" rupa-guna-lila-sphurti nama chhada haya na<br />rupa-guna-lila haite krsna-nama haya na [31]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sphurti</span>–Revelation [of Krishna’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">rupa</span>–form, <span class=\\"e2\\">guna</span>–qualities, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">lila</span>–Pastimes <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–does not occur <span class=\\"e2\\">chhada</span>–without <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–the Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–Krishna’s <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–Name <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–does not manifest <span class=\\"e2\\">haite</span>–from [His] <span class=\\"e2\\">rupa</span>–form, <span class=\\"e2\\">guna</span>–qualities, [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">lila</span>–Pastimes. [31]"},{"class":"b50","text":" Revelation of Krishna’s Form, Qualities, and Pastimes does not occur without the Name. Krishna’s Name does not manifest from His Form, Qualities, or Pastimes."},{"class":"b97","text":" রূপ হৈতে নাম-স্ফূর্ত্তি গুরু কভু বলে না<br />গুণ হৈতে নাম-স্ফূর্ত্তি গুরু কভু বলে না ॥৩২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" rupa haite nama-sphurti guru kabhu bale na<br />guna haite nama-sphurti guru kabhu bale na [32]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–A Guru <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says [there is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sphurti</span>–revelation <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–of [Krishna’s] Name <span class=\\"e2\\">haite</span>–from [His] <span class=\\"e2\\">rupa</span>–form. <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–A Guru <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says [there is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sphurti</span>–revelation <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–of [Krishna’s] Name <span class=\\"e2\\">haite</span>–from [His] <span class=\\"e2\\">guna</span>–qualities.[32]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A Guru never says there is revelation of Krishna’s Name from His form. A Guru never says there is revelation of Krishna’s Name from His qualities."},{"class":"b97","text":" লীলা হৈতে নাম-স্ফূর্ত্তি রূপানুগ বলে না<br />নাম-নামী দুই বস্তু রূপানুগ বলে না ॥৩৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" lila haite nama-sphurti rupanuga bale na<br />nama-nami dui vastu rupanuga bale na [33]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">rupanuga</span>–A follower of Sri Rupa <span class=\\"e2\\">bale na</span>–does not say [that there is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sphurti</span>–revelation [of Krishna’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–Name <span class=\\"e2\\">haite</span>–from [Krishna’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">lila</span>–Pastimes. <span class=\\"e2\\">rupanuga</span>–A follower of Sri Rupa <span class=\\"e2\\">bale na</span>–does not say [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–the Name [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nami</span>–the Named [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span>–two [different] <span class=\\"e2\\">vastu</span>–things. [33]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A follower of Sri Rupa does not say that there is revelation of Krishna’s Name from Krishna’s Pastimes. A follower of Sri Rupa does not say the Name and the Named (Krishna Himself) are two different things."},{"class":"b97","text":" রস আগে রতি পাছে রূপানুগ বলে না<br />রস আগে শ্রদ্ধা পাছে গুরু কভু বলে না ॥৩৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" rasa age rati pachhe rupanuga bale na<br />rasa age sraddha pachhe guru kabhu bale na [34]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">rupanuga</span>–A follower of Sri Rupa <span class=\\"e2\\">bale na</span>–does not say, <span class=\\"e2\\">age</span>–“First <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasa, <span class=\\"e2\\">pachhe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">rati</span>–rati.” <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–A Guru <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says, <span class=\\"e2\\">age</span>–“First <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasa, <span class=\\"e2\\">pachhe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">sraddha</span>–faith.” [34]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A follower of Sri Rupa does not say, “First rasa, then rati.” A Guru never says, “First rasa, then sraddha.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" রতি আগে শ্রদ্ধা পাছে রূপানুগ বলে না<br />ক্রম-পথ ছাড়ি’ সিদ্ধি রূপানুগ বলে না ॥৩৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" rati age sraddha pachhe rupanuga bale na<br />krama-patha chhadi’ siddhi rupanuga bale na [35]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">rupanuga</span>–A follower of Sri Rupa <span class=\\"e2\\">bale na</span>–does not say, <span class=\\"e2\\">age</span>–“First <span class=\\"e2\\">rati</span>–rati, <span class=\\"e2\\">pachhe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">sraddha</span>–faith.” <span class=\\"e2\\">rupanuga</span>–A follower of Sri Rupa <span class=\\"e2\\">bale na</span>–does not say, [there can be] <span class=\\"e2\\">siddhi</span>–perfection <span class=\\"e2\\">chhadi’</span>–by giving up <span class=\\"e2\\">krama</span>–the gradual <span class=\\"e2\\">patha</span>–path. [35]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A follower of Sri Rupa does not say, “First rati, then sraddha.” A follower of Sri Rupa does not say one can reach perfection by giving up the gradual path."},{"class":"b97","text":" মহাজন-পথ ছাড়ি’ নব্য-পথে ধায় না<br />অপরাধ-সহ নাম কখনই হয় না ॥৩৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" mahajana-patha chhadi’ navya-pathe dhaya na<br />aparadha-saha nama kakhanai haya na [36]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [A follower of Sri Rupa] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhadi’ na</span>–does not reject<span class=\\"e2\\"> patha</span>–the path <span class=\\"e2\\">mahajana</span>–of the great souls [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhaya</span>–run [down] <span class=\\"e2\\">navya</span>–a new <span class=\\"e2\\">pathe</span>–path. <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–The Name <span class=\\"e2\\">kakhanai na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–manifests <span class=\\"e2\\">saha</span>–in the midst <span class=\\"e2\\">aparadha</span>–of offences. [36]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A follower of Sri Rupa does not reject the path of the great souls and run down a new path. The Name never manifests in the midst of offences."},{"class":"b97","text":" নামে প্রাকৃতার্থ-বুদ্ধি ভক্ত কভু করে না<br />অপরাধযুক্ত নাম ভক্ত কভু লয় না ॥৩৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" name prakrtartha-buddhi bhakta kabhu kare na<br />aparadha-yukta nama bhakta kabhu laya na [37]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span>–A devotee <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhi kare</span>–thinks <span class=\\"e2\\">name</span>–the Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">artha</span>–something <span class=\\"e2\\">prakrta</span>–mundane. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span>–A devotee <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">laya</span>–takes <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">yukta</span>–with <span class=\\"e2\\">aparadha</span>–offences. [37]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A devotee never thinks the Name is something mundane. A devotee never chants the Name with offences."},{"class":"b97","text":" নামেতে প্রাকৃতবুদ্ধি রূপানুগ করে না<br />কৃষ্ণরূপে জড়বুদ্ধি রূপানুগ করে না ॥৩৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" namete prakrta-buddhi rupanuga kare na<br />krsna-rupe jada-buddhi rupanuga kare na [38]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">rupanuga</span>–A follower of Sri Rupa <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhi kare na</span>–does not think <span class=\\"e2\\">namete</span>–the Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">prakrta</span>–material. <span class=\\"e2\\">rupanuga</span>–A follower of Sri Rupa <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhi kare na</span>–does not think <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–Krishna’s <span class=\\"e2\\">rupe</span>–form [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–mundane. [38]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A follower of Sri Rupa does not think the Name is material. A follower of Sri Rupa does not think Krishna’s form is mundane."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণগুণে জড়বুদ্ধি রূপানুগ করে না<br />পরিকর-বৈশিষ্ট্যকে প্রাকৃত ত জানে না ॥৩৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" krsna-gune jada-buddhi rupanuga kare na<br />parikara-vaisistyake prakrta ta jane na [39]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">rupanuga</span>–A follower of Sri Rupa <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhi kare na</span>–does not think <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–Krishna’s <span class=\\"e2\\">gune</span>–qualities [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–mundane. [A follower of Sri Rupa] <span class=\\"e2\\">ta</span>–indeed <span class=\\"e2\\">jane na</span>–does not consider [Krishna’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">parikara</span>–associates [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vaisistyake</span>–unique characteristics [to be] <span class=\\"e2\\">prakrta</span>–material. [39]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A follower of Sri Rupa does not think Krishna’s qualities are mundane, and they do not consider Krishna’s associates and unique characteristics to be material."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণলীলা জড়তুল্য রূপানুগ বলে না<br />কৃষ্ণেতর ভোগ্য-বস্তু কৃষ্ণ কভু হয় না ॥৪০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" krsna-lila jada-tulya rupanuga bale na<br />krsnetara bhogya-vastu Krishna kabhu haya na [40]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">rupanuga</span>–A follower of Sri Rupa <span class=\\"e2\\">bale na</span>–does not say <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–Krishna’s <span class=\\"e2\\">lila</span>–Pastimes [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">tulya</span>–comparable <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–to matter. <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–Krishna <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–becomes <span class=\\"e2\\">vastu</span>–an object <span class=\\"e2\\">bhogya</span>–of enjoyment <span class=\\"e2\\">itara</span>–for anyone other than <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–Krishna. [40]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A follower of Sri Rupa does not say that Krishna’s Pastimes are comparable to material affairs. Krishna never becomes an object of enjoyment for anyone other than Himself."},{"class":"b97","text":" জড়কে অনর্থ ছাড়া আর কিছু মানে না<br />জড়াসক্তি-বশে রসে কৃষ্ণজ্ঞান করে না ॥৪১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jadake anartha chhada ara kichhu mane na<br />jadasakti-vase rase krsna-jnana kare na [41]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">mane na</span>–Do not consider [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">jadake</span>–matter [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">ara kichhu</span>–anything <span class=\\"e2\\">chhada</span>–other than <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–an anartha. <span class=\\"e2\\">jnana kare na</span>–Do not think <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–Krishna [is present] <span class=\\"e2\\">rase</span>–in rasa [that is] <span class=\\"e2\\">vase</span>–under the sway <span class=\\"e2\\">asakti</span>–of attachment <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–to matter. [41]"},{"class":"b50","text":" Do not consider that matter is anything other than an anartha. Do not think Krishna is present in rasa that is under the sway of material attachment."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণনাম কৃষ্ণরূপ কভু জড় বলে না<br />কৃষ্ণগুণ কৃষ্ণলীলা কভু জড় বলে না ॥৪২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" krsna-nama krsna-rupa kabhu jada bale na<br />krsna-guna krsna-lila kabhu jada bale na [42]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–Never <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–say [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–Krishna’s <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–Name [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–Krishna’s <span class=\\"e2\\">rupa</span>–form [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–material. <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–Never <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–say [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–Krishna’s <span class=\\"e2\\">guna</span>–qualities [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–Krishna’s <span class=\\"e2\\">lila</span>–Pastimes [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–material.[42]"},{"class":"b50","text":" Never say that Krishna’s Name or Krishna’s form are material. Never say that Krishna’s qualities or Krishna’s Pastimes are material."},{"class":"b97","text":" জড়রূপ অনর্থেতে কৃষ্ণ ভ্রম করে না<br />কৃষ্ণনামরূপগুণে জড়বুদ্ধি করে না ॥৪৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jada-rupa anarthete krsna bhrama kare na<br />krsna-nama-rupa-gune jada-buddhi kare na [43]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhrama kare na</span>–Do not confuse <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–Krishna <span class=\\"e2\\">anarthete</span>–with an anartha <span class=\\"e2\\">rupa</span>–in the form <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–of matter. <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhi kare na</span>–Do not think <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–Krishna’s <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">rupa</span>–form, [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">gune</span>–qualities [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–matter. [43]"},{"class":"b50","text":" Do not confuse Krishna with an anartha in the form of matter. Do not think Krishna’s Name, Form, or Qualities are material."},{"class":"b97","text":" নামরূপগুণলীলা জড় বলি’ মানে না<br />জড়নামরূপগুণে কৃষ্ণ কভু বলে না ॥৪৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nama-rupa-guna-lila jada bali’ mane na<br />jada-nama-rupa-gune krsna kabhu bale na [44]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’ mane na</span>–Do not consider [Krishna’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">rupa</span>–Form, <span class=\\"e2\\">guna</span>–Qualities, [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">lila</span>–Pastimes [to be] <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–matter. <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–Never <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–say [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–names, <span class=\\"e2\\">rupa</span>–forms, [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">gune</span>–qualities <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–of matter [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">krsna</span>–Krishna. [44]"},{"class":"b50","text":" Do not consider Krishna’s Name, Form, Qualities, or Pastimes material. Never say material names, forms, or qualities are Krishna."},{"class":"b97","text":" জড়শূন্য অপ্রাকৃত নাম ছাড়া বলে না<br />জড়শূন্য অপ্রাকৃত রূপ ছাড়া দেখে না ॥৪৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jada-sunya aprakrta nama chhada bale na<br />jada-sunya aprakrta rupa chhada dekhe na [45]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bale na</span>–Do not chant [anything] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhada</span>–other than <span class=\\"e2\\">aprakrta</span>–the supramundane <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">sunya</span>–free <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–from matter. <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhe na</span>–Do not see [anything] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhada</span>–other than <span class=\\"e2\\">aprakrta</span>–the supramundane <span class=\\"e2\\">rupa</span>–form [of Krishna,] <span class=\\"e2\\">sunya</span>–free <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–from matter. [45]"},{"class":"b50","text":" Do not chant anything other than the supramundane Name, free from matter. Do not see anything other than the supramundane form of Krishna, free from matter."},{"class":"b97","text":" জড়শূন্য অপ্রাকৃত গুণ ছাড়া শুনে না<br />জড়শূন্য অপ্রাকৃত লীলা ছাড়া সেবে না ॥৪৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jada-sunya aprakrta guna chhada sune na<br />jada-sunya aprakrta lila chhada seve na [46]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sune na</span>–Do not hear about [anything] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhada</span>–other than <span class=\\"e2\\">aprakrta</span>–the supramundane <span class=\\"e2\\">guna</span>–qualities [of Krishna,] <span class=\\"e2\\">sunya</span>–free <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–from matter. <span class=\\"e2\\">seva na</span>–Do not serve [anything] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhada</span>–other than <span class=\\"e2\\">aprakrta</span>–the supramundane <span class=\\"e2\\">lila</span>–Pastimes [of Krishna,] <span class=\\"e2\\">sunya</span>–free <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–from matter. [46]"},{"class":"b50","text":" Do not hear about anything other than the supramundane qualities of Krishna, free from matter. Do not serve anything other than the supramundane Pastimes of Krishna, free from matter."},{"class":"b97","text":" অনর্থ থাকার কালে জড়রূপে মজে না<br />অনর্থ থাকার কালে জড়গুণে মিশে না ॥৪৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" anartha thakara kale jada-rupe maje na<br />anartha thakara kale jada-gune mise na [47]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kale</span>–At the time [of] <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–anarthas <span class=\\"e2\\">thakara</span>–remaining, <span class=\\"e2\\">maje na</span>–do not take pleasure <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–in material <span class=\\"e2\\">rupe</span>–forms. <span class=\\"e2\\">kale</span>–At the time [of] <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–anarthas <span class=\\"e2\\">thakara</span>–remaining, <span class=\\"e2\\">mise na</span>–do not associate <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–with material <span class=\\"e2\\">gune</span>–qualities. [47]"},{"class":"b50","text":" While anarthas remain, do not take pleasure in material forms. While anarthas remain, do not associate with material qualities."},{"class":"b97","text":" অনর্থ থাকার কালে জড়লীলা ভোগে না<br />অনর্থ থাকার কালে শুদ্ধনাম ছাড়ে না ॥৪৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" anartha thakara kale jada-lila bhoge na<br />anartha thakara kale suddha-nama chhade na [48]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kale</span>–At the time [of] <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–anarthas <span class=\\"e2\\">thakara</span>–remaining, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhoge na</span>–do not enjoy <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–material <span class=\\"e2\\">lila</span>–pastimes. <span class=\\"e2\\">kale</span>–At the time [of] <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–anarthas <span class=\\"e2\\">thakara</span>–remaining, <span class=\\"e2\\">chhade na</span>–do not give up <span class=\\"e2\\">suddha</span>–the pure <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–Name. [48]"},{"class":"b50","text":" While anarthas remain, do not enjoy material pastimes. While anarthas remain, do not give up the pure Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" অনর্থ থাকার কালে রসগান করে না<br />অনর্থ থাকার কালে সিদ্ধিলব্ধ বলে না ॥৪৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" anartha thakara kale rasa-gana kare na<br />anartha thakara kale siddhi-labdha bale na [49]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kale</span>–At the time [of] <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–anarthas <span class=\\"e2\\">thakara</span>–remaining, <span class=\\"e2\\">gana kare na</span>–do not sing <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–about rasa. <span class=\\"e2\\">kale</span>–At the time [of] <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–anarthas <span class=\\"e2\\">thakara</span>–remaining, <span class=\\"e2\\">bale na</span>–do not say [you have] <span class=\\"e2\\">labdha</span>–attained <span class=\\"e2\\">siddhi</span>–perfection. [49]"},{"class":"b50","text":" While anarthas remain, do not sing about rasa. While anarthas remain, do not say that you have attained perfection."},{"class":"b97","text":" অনর্থ থাকার কালে লীলাগান করে না<br />অনর্থনিবৃত্তিকালে নামে জড় বলে না ॥৫০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" anartha thakara kale lila-gana kare na<br />anartha-nivrtti-kale name jada bale na [50]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kale</span>–At the time [of] <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–anarthas <span class=\\"e2\\">thakara</span>–remaining, <span class=\\"e2\\">gana kare na</span>–do not sing <span class=\\"e2\\">lila</span>–about [the Lord’s] Pastimes. <span class=\\"e2\\">kale</span>–At the time<span class=\\"e2\\"> nivrtti</span>–of the cessation <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–of anarthas, <span class=\\"e2\\">bale na</span>–one does not say <span class=\\"e2\\">name</span>–the Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–material. [50]"},{"class":"b50","text":" While anarthas remain, do not sing about the Lord’s Pastimes. Once anarthas have ceased, one does not say the Name is material."},{"class":"b97","text":" অনর্থনিবৃত্তিকালে রূপে জড় দেখে না<br />অনর্থনিবৃত্তিকালে গুণে জড় বুঝে না ॥৫১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" anartha-nivrtti-kale rupe jada dekhe na<br />anartha-nivrtti-kale gune jada bujhe na [51]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kale</span>–At the time<span class=\\"e2\\"> nivrtti</span>–of the cessation <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–of anarthas, <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhe na</span>–one does not see [the Lord’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">rupe</span>–form [to be] <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–material. <span class=\\"e2\\">kale</span>–At the time<span class=\\"e2\\"> nivrtti</span>–of the cessation <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–of anarthas, <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhe na</span>–one does not understand [the Lord’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">gune</span>–qualities [to be] <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–material. [51]"},{"class":"b50","text":" Once anarthas have ceased, one does not see the Lord’s form to be material. Once anarthas have ceased, one does not understand the Lord’s qualities to be material."},{"class":"b97","text":" অনর্থনিবৃত্তিকালে জড় লীলা সেবে না<br />রূপানুগ গুরুদেব শিষ্যহিংসা করে না ॥৫২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" anartha-nivrtti-kale jada lila seve na<br />rupanuga gurudeva sisya-himsa kare na [52]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kale</span>–At the time<span class=\\"e2\\"> nivrtti</span>–of the cessation <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–of anarthas, <span class=\\"e2\\">seve na</span>–one does not participate in <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–mundane <span class=\\"e2\\">lila</span>–pastimes. <span class=\\"e2\\">gurudeva</span>–A Guru [who is] <span class=\\"e2\\">rupanuga</span>–a follower of Sri Rupa <span class=\\"e2\\">himsa kare na</span>–does not abuse [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">sisya</span>–disciples. [52]"},{"class":"b50","text":" Once anarthas have ceased, one does not participate in mundane pastimes. A Guru following Sri Rupa does not abuse their disciples."},{"class":"b97","text":" গুরু ত্যজি’ জড়ে আশা কভু ভক্ত করে না<br />মহাজন-পথে দোষ কভু গুরু দেয় না ॥৫৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" guru tyaji’ jade asa kabhu bhakta kare na<br />mahajana-pathe dosa kabhu guru deya na [53]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span>–A devotee <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">tyaji’</span>–rejects [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–Guru [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">asa kare</span>–desires <span class=\\"e2\\">jade</span>–the mundane. <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–A Guru <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">dosa deya na</span>–criticises <span class=\\"e2\\">pathe</span>–to the path <span class=\\"e2\\">mahajana</span>–of the great souls. [53]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A devotee never rejects their Guru and desires the mundane. A Guru never criticises the path of the great souls."},{"class":"b97","text":" গুরু-মহাজন-বাক্যে ভেদ কভু হয় না<br />সাধনের পথে কা̐টা সদ্গুরু দেয় না ॥৫৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" guru-mahajana-vakye bheda kabhu haya na<br />sadhanera pathe ka̐ta sad-guru deya na [54]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bheda</span>–Differences <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu na</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–arise <span class=\\"e2\\">vakye</span>–between the statements <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–of a Guru [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">mahajana</span>–the great souls. <span class=\\"e2\\">sad-guru</span>–A true Guru <span class=\\"e2\\">deya na</span>–does not put <span class=\\"e2\\">ka̐ta</span>–thorns <span class=\\"e2\\">pathe</span>–on the path <span class=\\"e2\\">sadhanera</span>–of practice. [54]"},{"class":"b50","text":" There are never any differences between the statements of a Guru and the great souls. A true Guru does not put thorns on the path of sadhana."},{"class":"b97","text":" অধিকার অবিচার রূপানুগ করে না<br />অনর্থ-অন্বিত দাসে রসশিক্ষা দেয় না ॥৫৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" adhikara avichara rupanuga kare na<br />anartha-anvita dase rasa-siksa deya na [55]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">rupanuga</span>–A follower of Sri Rupa <span class=\\"e2\\">avichara kare na</span>–does not neglect to consider <span class=\\"e2\\">adhikara</span>–the qualifications [of others and] <span class=\\"e2\\">deya na</span>–does not give <span class=\\"e2\\">siksa</span>–instructions <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–about rasa <span class=\\"e2\\">dase</span>–to servants [who are] <span class=\\"e2\\">anvita</span>–ridden <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–with vices. [55]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A follower of Sri Rupa does not neglect to consider the qualification of others and does not give instructions about rasa to servants who are ridden with anarthas."},{"class":"b97","text":" ভাগবত পদ্য বলি’ কুব্যাখ্যা ত করে না<br />লোকসংগ্রহে তরে ক্রম-পথ ছাড়ে না ॥৫৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhagavata padya bali’ kuvyakhya ta kare na<br />loka-sangrahera tare krama-patha chhade na [56]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [A follower of Sri Rupa] <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’ na</span>–does not recite <span class=\\"e2\\">padya</span>–verses <span class=\\"e2\\">bhagavata</span>–of <span class=\\"e3\\">Srimad Bhagavatam</span> [and then] <span class=\\"e2\\">ta</span>–indeed <span class=\\"e2\\">kuvyakhya kare</span>–misinterpret [them]. [A follower of Sri Rupa] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhade na</span>–does not reject <span class=\\"e2\\">krama</span>–the gradual <span class=\\"e2\\">patha</span>–path <span class=\\"e2\\">tare</span>–to <span class=\\"e2\\">sangrahera</span>–amass <span class=\\"e2\\">loka</span>–followers. [56]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A follower of Sri Rupa does not recite verses of <span class=\\"e3\\">Srimad Bhagavatam</span> and then misinterpret them. A follower of Sri Rupa does not reject the gradual path to amass followers."},{"class":"b97","text":" না উঠিয়া বৃক্ষোপরি ফল ধরি’ টানে না<br />রূপানুগ ক্রম-পথ বিলোপ ত করে না ॥৫৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" na uthiya vrksopari phala dhari’ tane na<br />rupanuga krama-patha vilopa ta kare na [57]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [A follower of Sri Rupa] <span class=\\"e2\\">uthiya na</span>–does not climb <span class=\\"e2\\">upari</span>–up <span class=\\"e2\\">vrksa</span>–the tree [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhari’ tane</span>–forcibly grab <span class=\\"e2\\">phala</span>–the fruit. <span class=\\"e2\\">rupanuga</span>–A follower of Sri Rupa <span class=\\"e2\\">ta</span>–indeed <span class=\\"e2\\">vilopa kare na</span>–does not abolish <span class=\\"e2\\">krama</span>–the gradual <span class=\\"e2\\">patha</span>–path. [57]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A follower of Sri Rupa does not climb up the tree and forcibly grab the fruit. A follower of Sri Rupa does not abolish the gradual path."},{"class":"b97","text":" অনর্থকে অর্থ বলি’ কুপথেতে লয় না<br />প্রাকৃত-সহজ-মত অপ্রাকৃত বলে না ॥৫৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" anarthake artha bali’ kupathete laya na<br />prakrta-sahaja-mata aprakrta bale na [58]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [A follower of Sri Rupa] <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’ na</span>–does not consider <span class=\\"e2\\">anarthake</span>–vices [to be their] <span class=\\"e2\\">artha</span>–desired end [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">laya</span>–take to <span class=\\"e2\\">kupathete</span>–the wrong path. [A follower of Sri Rupa] <span class=\\"e2\\">bale na</span>–does not consider <span class=\\"e2\\">prakrta-sahaja-mata</span>–mundane imitationism [to be] <span class=\\"e2\\">aprakrta</span>–supramundane. [58]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A follower of Sri Rupa does not consider anarthas to be one’s desired end. A follower of Sri Rupa does not consider mundane imitationism (prakrta sahajiyaism) to be supramundane."},{"class":"b97","text":" অনর্থ না গেলে শিষ্যে জাতরতি বলে না<br />অনর্থবিশিষ্ট শিষ্যে রসতত্ত্ব বলে না ॥৫৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" anartha na gele sisye jata-rati bale na<br />anartha-visista sisye rasa-tattva bale na [59]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [If their] <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–anarthas <span class=\\"e2\\">gele na</span>–have not gone away, [a follower of Sri Rupa] <span class=\\"e2\\">bale na</span>–does not say <span class=\\"e2\\">sisye</span>–a disciple [has] <span class=\\"e2\\">jata</span>–developed <span class=\\"e2\\">rati</span>–rati. [A follower of Sri Rupa] <span class=\\"e2\\">bale na</span>–does not speak <span class=\\"e2\\">tattva</span>–about the science <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–of rasa <span class=\\"e2\\">sisye</span>–with a disciple <span class=\\"e2\\">visista</span>–ridden <span class=\\"e2\\">anartha</span>–with anarthas. [59]"},{"class":"b50","text":" If their anarthas have not gone away, a follower of Sri Rupa does not say a disciple has developed rati. A follower of Sri Rupa does not speak about the science of rasa with a disciple ridden with anarthas."},{"class":"b97","text":" অশক্ত কোমলশ্রদ্ধে রসকথা বলে না<br />অনধিকারীরে রসে অধিকার দেয় না ॥৬০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" asakta komala-sraddhe rasa-katha bale na<br />anadhikarire rase adhikara deya na [60]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [A follower of Sri Rupa] <span class=\\"e2\\">katha bale na</span>–does not discuss <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasa [with someone who is] <span class=\\"e2\\">asakta</span>–incapable [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">komala</span>–of soft <span class=\\"e2\\">sraddhe</span>–faith. [A follower of Sri Rupa] <span class=\\"e2\\">deya na</span>–does not try to give <span class=\\"e2\\">adhikara</span>–the qualification <span class=\\"e2\\">rase</span>–for rasa <span class=\\"e2\\">anadhikarire</span>–to those who are unqualified. [60]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A follower of Sri Rupa does not discuss rasa with someone who is incapable and of soft faith. A follower of Sri Rupa does not try to give the qualification for rasa to those who are unqualified."},{"class":"b97","text":" বৈধভক্তজনে কভু রাগানুগ জানে না<br />কোমলশ্রদ্ধকে কভু রসিক ত জানে না ॥৬১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vaidha-bhakta-jane kabhu raganuga jane na<br />komala-sraddhake kabhu rasika ta jane na [61]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [A follower of Sri Rupa] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu jane na</span>–never thinks <span class=\\"e2\\">vaidha</span>–regulated <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta-jane</span>–devotees [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">raganuga</span>–raganuga-bhaktas. <span class=\\"e2\\">ta</span>–Indeed, [a follower of Sri Rupa] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu jane na</span>–never thinks [those] <span class=\\"e2\\">komala</span>–with soft <span class=\\"e2\\">sraddhake</span>–faith [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">rasika</span>–relishers of rasa. [61]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A follower of Sri Rupa never thinks vaidha-bhaktas are raganuga-bhaktas. A follower of Sri Rupa never thinks those with soft faith are rasikas."},{"class":"b97","text":" স্বল্পশ্রদ্ধজনে কভু জাতরতি মানে না<br />স্বল্পশ্রদ্ধজনে রস উপদেশ করে না ॥৬২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" svalpa-sraddha-jane kabhu jata-rati mane na<br />svalpa-sraddha-jane rasa upadesa kare na [62]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [A follower of Sri Rupa] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu mane na</span>–never thinks <span class=\\"e2\\">jane</span>–persons <span class=\\"e2\\">svalpa</span>–with little <span class=\\"e2\\">sraddha</span>–faith [have] <span class=\\"e2\\">jata</span>–developed <span class=\\"e2\\">rati</span>–rati, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">upadesa kare na</span>–does not instruct <span class=\\"e2\\">jane</span>–persons <span class=\\"e2\\">svalpa</span>–with little <span class=\\"e2\\">sraddha</span>–faith <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–about rasa. [62]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A follower of Sri Rupa never thinks those who have little faith have developed rati and does not instruct those who have little faith about rasa."},{"class":"b97","text":" জাতরতি প্রৌঢশ্রদ্ধসঙ্গ ত্যাগ করে না<br />কোমলশ্রদ্ধেরে কভু রস দিয়া সেবে না ॥৬৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jata-rati praudha-sraddha-sanga tyaga kare na<br />komala-sraddhere kabhu rasa diya seve na [63]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jata</span>–One who has developed <span class=\\"e2\\">rati</span>–rati <span class=\\"e2\\">tyaga kare na</span>–does not give up <span class=\\"e2\\">sanga</span>–the association [of persons with] <span class=\\"e2\\">praudha</span>–strong <span class=\\"e2\\">sraddha</span>–faith [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu diya na</span>–never gives <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasa [to or] <span class=\\"e2\\">seve</span>–serves [those who have] <span class=\\"e2\\">komala</span>–soft <span class=\\"e2\\">sraddhere</span>–faith. [63]"},{"class":"b50","text":" One who has developed rati does not give up the association of those who have strong faith and never gives rasa to or serves those who have soft faith."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণের সেবন লাগি’ জড়রসে মিশে না<br />রসোদয়ে কোন জীবে শিষ্যবুদ্ধি করে না ॥৬৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" krsnera sevana lagi’ jada-rase mise na<br />rasodaye kona jive sisya-buddhi kare na [64]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [One who has developed rati] <span class=\\"e2\\">mise na</span>–does not engage in <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–material <span class=\\"e2\\">rase</span>–pleasures <span class=\\"e2\\">lagi’</span>–for the sake <span class=\\"e2\\">krsnera</span>–of Krishna’s <span class=\\"e2\\">sevana</span>–service, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">udaye</span>–after the arising <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–of rasa [within them], <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhi kare na</span>–they do not consider <span class=\\"e2\\">kona</span>–any <span class=\\"e2\\">jive</span>–soul [to be] <span class=\\"e2\\">sisya</span>–a disciple. [64]"},{"class":"b50","text":" One who has developed rati does not engage in material pleasures for the sake of Krishna’s service, and once rasa has arisen within them, they do not consider any soul to be a disciple."},{"class":"b97","text":" রসিক-ভকতরাজ কভু শিষ্য করে না<br />রসিকজনের শিষ্য এই ভাব ছাড়ে না ॥৬৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" rasika-bhakata-raja kabhu sisya kare na<br />rasika-janera sisya ei bhava chhade na [65]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">raja</span>–The best <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakata</span>–of the devotees [who are] <span class=\\"e2\\">rasika</span>–relishers of rasa <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu kare na</span>–never make <span class=\\"e2\\">sisya</span>–disciples, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhade na</span>–they do not give up <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–the <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava</span>–attitude [of being] <span class=\\"e2\\">sisya</span>–the disciple <span class=\\"e2\\">janera</span>–of a person [who is] <span class=\\"e2\\">rasika</span>–a relisher of rasa. [65]"},{"class":"b50","text":" The best rasika-bhaktas never make disciples and do not give up the mentality that they are the disciple of a rasika-bhakta."},{"class":"b97","text":" সাধন ছাড়িলে ভাব উদয় ত হয় না<br />রাগানুগ জানিলেই সাধন ত ছাড়ে না ॥৬৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sadhana chhadile bhava udaya ta haya na<br />raganuga janilei sadhana ta chhade na [66]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">chhadile</span>–If one gives up <span class=\\"e2\\">sadhana</span>–the practice, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava</span>–bhava <span class=\\"e2\\">ta</span>–indeed <span class=\\"e2\\">udaya haya na</span>–does not arise, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">janilei</span>–even if one knows <span class=\\"e2\\">raganuga</span>–a raganuga-bhakta, <span class=\\"e2\\">ta</span>–indeed <span class=\\"e2\\">chhade na</span>–one does not give up [one’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadhana</span>–practice. [66]"},{"class":"b50","text":" If one gives up sadhana, bhava does not arise, and even if one knows a raganuga-bhakta, one does not give up one’s sadhana."},{"class":"b97","text":" ভাব না হইলে কভু রসোদয় হয় না<br />আগে রসোদয় পরে রত্যুদয় হয় না ॥৬৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhava na ha-ile kabhu rasodaya haya na<br />age rasodaya pare ratyudaya haya na [67]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [If] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava</span>–bhava <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ile na</span>–has not arisen, [then] <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasa <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu udaya haya na</span>–will never arise. <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–It is not [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">age</span>–first <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasa <span class=\\"e2\\">udaya</span>–arises [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pare</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">rati</span>–rati <span class=\\"e2\\">udaya</span>–arises. [67]"},{"class":"b50","text":" If bhava has not arisen, then rasa will never arise. It is not that rasa arises first and then rati arises."},{"class":"b97","text":" আগে রত্যুদয় পরে শ্রদ্ধোদয় হয় না<br />রসাভিষ্ট লভি’ পরে সাধন ত হয় না ॥৬৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" age ratyudaya pare sraddhodaya haya na<br />rasabhista labhi’ pare sadhana ta haya na [68]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–It is not [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">age</span>–first <span class=\\"e2\\">rati</span>–rati <span class=\\"e2\\">udaya</span>–arises [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pare</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">sraddha</span>–faith <span class=\\"e2\\">udaya</span>–arises. <span class=\\"e2\\">ta</span>–Indeed <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–it is not [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">labhi’</span>–one attains [one’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">abhista</span>–desired <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasa [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pare</span>–then [takes up] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadhana</span>–the practice. [68]"},{"class":"b50","text":" It is not that rati arises first and then sraddha arises. It is not that one attains one’s desired rasa and then takes up sadhana."},{"class":"b97","text":" সামগ্রীর অমিলনে স্থায়ীভাব হয় না<br />স্থায়ীভাব-ব্যতিরেকে রসে স্থিতি হয় না ॥৬৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" samagrira amilane sthayi-bhava haya na<br />sthayi-bhava-vyatireke rase sthiti haya na [69]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">amilane</span>–Without the gathering <span class=\\"e2\\">samagrira</span>–of ingredients, [one’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">sthayi-bhava</span>–foundational bhava <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–does not arise. <span class=\\"e2\\">vyatireke</span>–In the absence [of one’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">sthayi-bhava</span>–foundational bhava, <span class=\\"e2\\">sthiti haya na</span>–one does not become immersed <span class=\\"e2\\">rase</span>–in rasa. [69]"},{"class":"b50","text":" Without bringing together the necessary ingredients, sthayi-bhava does not arise. In the absence of sthayi-bhava, one does not become immersed in rasa."},{"class":"b97","text":" ভোগে মন জড়ে শ্রদ্ধা চিৎ প্রকাশ করে না<br />নামে শ্রদ্ধা না হইলে জড়বুদ্ধি ছাড়ে না ॥৭০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhoge mana jade sraddha chit prakasa kare na<br />name sraddha na ha-ile jada-buddhi chhade na [70]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">mana</span>–A mind [immersed] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhoge</span>–in enjoyment [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sraddha</span>–faith <span class=\\"e2\\">jade</span>–in the mundane <span class=\\"e2\\">prakasa are na</span>–do not manifest <span class=\\"e2\\">chit</span>–spirit. <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ile na</span>–If one does not develop <span class=\\"e2\\">sraddha</span>–faith <span class=\\"e2\\">name</span>–in the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">chhade na</span>–one will not give up [one’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–mundane <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhi</span>–mentality. [70]"},{"class":"b50","text":" A mind immersed in enjoyment and faith in the mundane do not manifest spirit. If one does not develop faith in the Name, one will not give up one’s mundane mentality."},{"class":"b97","text":" জড়বুদ্ধি না ছাড়িলে নাম কৃপা করে না<br />নাম কৃপা না করিলে লীলা শুনা য়ায় না ॥৭১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jada-buddhi na chhadile nama krpa kare na<br />nama krpa na karile lila suna yaya na [71]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">chhadile na</span>–If one does not give up [one’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–mundane <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhi</span>–mentality, <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">krpa kare na</span>–does not bless [them, and if] <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">krpa na karile</span>–does not bless [them, the Lord’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">lila</span>–Pastimes <span class=\\"e2\\">suna yaya na</span>–cannot be heard. [71]"},{"class":"b50","text":" If one does not give up one’s mundane mentality, the Name does not bless them, and if the Name does not bless them, the Lord’s Pastimes cannot be heard."},{"class":"b97","text":" নামকে জানিলে জড় কাম দূর হয় না<br />রূপকে মানিলে জড় কাম দূর হয় না ॥৭২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" namake janile jada kama dura haya na<br />rupake manile jada kama dura haya na [72]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">janile</span>–If one thinks <span class=\\"e2\\">namake</span>–the Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–mundane, <span class=\\"e2\\">kama</span>–material desires <span class=\\"e2\\">dura hay na</span>–do not go away. <span class=\\"e2\\">manile</span>–If one considers [the Lord’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">rupake</span>–form <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–mundane, <span class=\\"e2\\">kama</span>–material desires <span class=\\"e2\\">dura hay na</span>–do not go away. [72]"},{"class":"b50","text":" If one thinks the Name is mundane, material desires do not go away. If one considers the Lord’s form mundane, material desires do not go away."},{"class":"b97","text":" গুণকে বুঝিলে জড় কাম দূর হয় না<br />লীলাকে পূরিলে জড়ে কাম দূর হয় না ॥৭৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gunake bujhile jada kama dura haya na<br />lilake purile jade kama dura haya na [73]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhile</span>–If one considers [the Lord’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">gunake</span>–qualities <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–mundane, <span class=\\"e2\\">kama</span>–material desires <span class=\\"e2\\">dura hay na</span>–do not go away. <span class=\\"e2\\">purile</span>–If one fills [the Lord’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">lilake</span>–Pastimes <span class=\\"e2\\">jade</span>–with the mundane, <span class=\\"e2\\">kama</span>–material desires <span class=\\"e2\\">dura hay na</span>–do not go away.[73]"},{"class":"b50","text":" If one considers the Lord’s qualities mundane, material desires do not go away. If one fills the Lord’s Pastimes with the mundane, material desires do not go away."},{"class":"b97","text":" নামে জড়-ব্যবধানে রূপোদয় হয় না<br />নামে জড়-ব্যবধানে গুণোদয় হয় না<br />জড়ভোগ-ব্যবধানে লীলোদয় হয় না ॥৭৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" name jada-vyavadhane rupodaya haya na<br />name jada-vyavadhane gunodaya haya na<br />jada-bhoga-vyavadhane lilodaya haya na [74]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [The Lord’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">rupa</span>–form <span class=\\"e2\\">udaya haya na</span>–does not manifest <span class=\\"e2\\">name</span>–through the Name [when one is] <span class=\\"e2\\">vyavadhane</span>–under the cover <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–of the mundane. [The Lord’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">guna</span>–qualities <span class=\\"e2\\">udaya haya na</span>–do not manifest <span class=\\"e2\\">name</span>–through the Name [when one is] <span class=\\"e2\\">vyavadhane</span>–under the cover <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–of the mundane. [The Lord’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">lila</span>–Pastimes <span class=\\"e2\\">udaya haya na</span>–do not manifest [when one is] <span class=\\"e2\\">vyavadhane</span>–under the cover <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–of material. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhoga</span>–enjoyment. [74]"},{"class":"b50","text":" The Lord’s form does not manifest through the Name when one is covered over by the mundane, the Lord’s qualities do not manifest through the Name when one is covered over by the mundane, and the Lord’s Pastimes do not manifest when one is covered over by material enjoyment."},{"class":"b97","text":" অপরাধ-ব্যবধানে রসলাভ হয় না<br />অপরাধ-ব্যবধানে নাম কভু হয় না ॥৭৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" aparadha-vyavadhane rasa-labha haya na<br />aparadha-vyavadhane nama kabhu haya na [75]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–Rasa <span class=\\"e2\\">labha haya na</span>–is not attained [when one is] <span class=\\"e2\\">vyavadhane</span>–under the cover <span class=\\"e2\\">aparadha</span>–of offence. <span class=\\"e2\\">nama</span>–The Name <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu haya na</span>–never manifests [when one is] <span class=\\"e2\\">vyavadhane</span>–under the cover <span class=\\"e2\\">aparadha</span>–of offence. [75]"},{"class":"b50","text":" Rasa is not attained when one is covered over by offences. The Name never manifests when one is covered over by offences."},{"class":"b97","text":" ব্যবহিত লীলাগানে কাম দূর হয় না<br />অপরাধ-ব্যবধানে সিদ্ধদেহ পায় না ॥৭৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vyavahita lila-gane kama dura haya na<br />aparadha-vyavadhane siddha-deha paya na [76]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [When one is] <span class=\\"e2\\">vyavahita</span>–covered over, <span class=\\"e2\\">kama</span>–material desires <span class=\\"e2\\">dura haya na</span>–do not go away <span class=\\"e2\\">gane</span>–through songs [about the Lord’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">lila</span>–Pastimes. [When one is] <span class=\\"e2\\">vyavadhane</span>–under the cover <span class=\\"e2\\">aparadha</span>–of offences, <span class=\\"e2\\">paya na</span>–one does not attain [one’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">siddha</span>–spiritual <span class=\\"e2\\">deha</span>–form. [76]"},{"class":"b50","text":" When one is covered over, material desires do not go away through songs about the Lord’s Pastimes. When one is covered over by offences, one does not attain one’s spiritual form."},{"class":"b97","text":" সেবোপকরণ কর্ণে না শুনিলে হয় না<br />জড়োপকরণ দেহে লীলা শোনা য়ায় না ॥৭৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sevopakarana karne na sunile haya na<br />jadopakarana dehe lila sona yaya na [77]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sunile na</span>–If one does not listen <span class=\\"e2\\">karne</span>–with an ear [that is] <span class=\\"e2\\">upakarana</span>–an instrument <span class=\\"e2\\">seva</span>–for service, <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–one attains nothing. [The Lord’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">lila</span>–Pastimes <span class=\\"e2\\">sona yaya na</span>–cannot be heard <span class=\\"e2\\">dehe</span>–with a body [that is an] <span class=\\"e2\\">upakarana</span>–instrument <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–for the mundane. [77]"},{"class":"b50","text":" If one does not listen with an ear that is an instrument for service, one attains nothing. The Lord’s Pastimes cannot be heard with a body that is an instrument for the mundane."},{"class":"b97","text":" সেবায় উন্মুখ হলে জড়কথা হয় না<br />নতুবা চিন্ময়কথা কভু শ্রুত হয় না ॥৭৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sevaya unmukha hale jada-katha haya na<br />natuva chinmaya-katha kabhu sruta haya na [78]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hale</span>–If one is <span class=\\"e2\\">unmukha</span>–inclined <span class=\\"e2\\">sevaya</span>–towards service, <span class=\\"e2\\">haya na</span>–there is no <span class=\\"e2\\">jada</span>–mundane <span class=\\"e2\\">katha</span>–discussion. [If one is inclined] <span class=\\"e2\\">natuva</span>–otherwise, <span class=\\"e2\\">chinmaya</span>–spiritual <span class=\\"e2\\">katha</span>–discussion <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu sruta haya na</span>–is never heard. [78]"},{"class":"b55","text":" If one is inclined towards service, one does not engage in mundane discussion. If one is inclined otherwise, one never listens to spiritual discussion."}]}]}')}}]);
